###########################################################################################
# PARAMETERS' DEFINITION FOR THE BAKRYUN NETWORK
# Source: Lee and Lee (2001), BakRyun water distribution network, South Korea
# 35 nodes, 58 pipes, 17 loops
# Gravity-fed from reservoir at Node 1 with fixed head = 58.0 m
# Hazen-Williams coefficient C = 100 for all pipes
# Minimum pressure head = 15 m above ground level
# Objective: determine diameters of new pipes (1-3) and parallel pipes (4-9)
# Demands converted from cmd (m^3/day) to m^3/s (divided by 86400)
#
# Paper Link : https://www.osti.gov/etdeweb/biblio/20294474
# Reference paper : https://www.tandfonline.com/doi/full/10.1080/03052150500467430
###########################################################################################

# Node's parameters: elevation (m), demand (m^3/s), minimum pressure (m), maximum pressure (m)
# Node 1  = reservoir, fixed head = 58.0 m, no demand
# Node 34 = junction, no demand
#param: nodes:      E      D                   P    pmax :=
